+# Migrating away from React.FC
+
+Per ADR006, new components should not use `React.FC`. If you have legacy
+components that look like this:
+
+```tsx
+/* Legacy pattern — do not copy */
+const MyCard: React.FC<MyCardProps> = ({ title, children }) => (
+  <Card title={title}>{children}</Card>
+);
+```
+
+rewrite them to type props explicitly:
+
+```tsx
+type MyCardProps = PropsWithChildren<{ title: string }>;
+const MyCard = ({ title, children }: MyCardProps) => (
+  <Card title={title}>{children}</Card>
+);
+```
